# DEFINES
PROVIDER Openrouter
API_KEY sk-hypercanvas-ea5ae94a72a89e837e07a226742cfb68cc67d2c327570c24
# API_URL https://claude-oauth-api-production.up.railway.app/api/v1
API_URL https://claude-oauth-api-0xtayzon-production.up.railway.app/api/v1
PROMPT_ENGINEER_MODEL anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5
# PROMPT_ENGINEER_MODEL anthropic/claude-opus-4-6
RUN_BIN claude --dangerously-skip-permissions --effort max --model claude-haiku-4-5
EVAL_BIN claude --dangerously-skip-permissions --effort max --model claude-haiku-4-5
DIR ~/circuitsort
CHECKPOINT on

# Build a novel sorting algorithm that beats quicksort on real-world data
CIRCUIT Build a sorting algorithm that consistently beats std lib sort on real-world benchmarks:
  RUN Create a novel sorting algorithm in Rust that outperforms the standard library sort (pdqsort/TimSort hybrid) \
    on real-world data distributions. The algorithm must handle all of: nearly-sorted data, reverse-sorted data, \
    data with many duplicates, random uniform data, and zipfian-distributed data. \
    Build a comprehensive benchmark suite that tests arrays of sizes 100, 10000, and 1000000 elements \
    across all distributions. The algorithm must be faster than std sort on at least 80% of benchmark cases. \
    Include proper statistical measurement with multiple iterations per benchmark.
  EVAL Run the full benchmark suite (cargo bench or cargo run --release). \
    Verify that the custom sort beats std sort on at least 80% of the benchmark cases. \
    Check that the algorithm is correct (sorted output matches std sort output for all test cases). \
    Check that it handles edge cases: empty arrays, single element, all identical elements, i32::MIN and i32::MAX values.
    RETRY 10
